<div id="review_3678832142" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3678832142" />
    <a title="Kelly L Hobbins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27030881-kelly-l-hobbins"><img alt="Kelly L Hobbins" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3678832142?book_show_action=true">Dec 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly L Hobbins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly L Hobbins" href="/user/show/27030881-kelly-l-hobbins">Kelly L Hobbins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3678832142&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3678832142" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11898344609020792689">This was a book about a South African boy who grew up impoverished under the apartheid system in the 70&apos;s. It was VERY detailed and long. I am glad I listened to it instead of read it. It was extremely interesting and enlightening. We all know the basic apartheid principles, but this really showed me the horrific truths of life for a black person living in South Africa. However, as depressing as this story could be, at times, it was still inspiring because Mr. Mathabane, who read the audio book </span>
  <span id="freeText11898344609020792689" style="display:none">This was a book about a South African boy who grew up impoverished under the apartheid system in the 70's. It was VERY detailed and long. I am glad I listened to it instead of read it. It was extremely interesting and enlightening. We all know the basic apartheid principles, but this really showed me the horrific truths of life for a black person living in South Africa. However, as depressing as this story could be, at times, it was still inspiring because Mr. Mathabane, who read the audio book himself, used education and tennis to lift himself out of this oppressive life. Thanks to some help along the way from blacks and whites alike, in the end, he fulfills his dream of coming to America. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11898344609020792689" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3678832142">
  <td colspan="2">
